#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.normal:2
msgid "Draw random samples from a normal (Gaussian) distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.normal:4
msgid ""
"The probability density function of the normal distribution, first derived "
"by De Moivre and 200 years later by both Gauss and Laplace independently "
"[Ra2e838c5ea87-2]_, is often called the bell curve because of its "
"characteristic shape (see the example below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.normal:9
msgid ""
"The normal distributions occurs often in nature.  For example, it describes "
"the commonly occurring distribution of samples influenced by a large number "
"of tiny, random disturbances, each with its own unique distribution "
"[Ra2e838c5ea87-2]_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.normal:15
msgid ""
"New code should use the `~numpy.random.Generator.normal` method of a `~numpy."
"random.Generator` instance instead; please see the :ref:`random-quick-start`."
msgstr ""

